{"id":57,"parent_id":52,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":57,"title":"Exodus 5","subtitle":"","short_title":"Ex.","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 5"],[".studySummary",["i","Moses and Aaron ask Pharaoh to free Israel—Pharaoh responds, Who is the Lord?—He places greater burdens upon the children of Israel."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.1","order":"02.03.005.5056"},["b","1"],"And afterward Moses and Aaron went in, and told Pharaoh, Thus saith the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"God of Israel,",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"Let"],"my people",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_1b"},"go"],", that they may hold a",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_1c"},"feast"],"unto me in the wilderness."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.2","order":"02.03.005.5057"},["b","2"],"And Pharaoh said, Who",["i","is"],"the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", that I should",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_2a"},"obey"],"his voice to let Israel go? I",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_2b"},"know not"],"the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", neither will I let Israel go."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.3","order":"02.03.005.5058"},["b","3"],"And they said, The",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"God"],"of the Hebrews hath met with us: let us go, we pray thee, three days’ journey into the desert, and sacrifice unto the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"our God; lest he fall upon us with pestilence, or with the sword."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.4","order":"02.03.005.5059"},["b","4"],"And the king of Egypt said unto them, Wherefore do ye, Moses and Aaron,",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_4a"},"let"],"the people from their works? get you unto your",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_4b"},"burdens"],"."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.5","order":"02.03.005.5060"},["b","5"],"And Pharaoh said, Behold, the people of the land now",["i","are"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"many"],", and ye make them rest from their burdens."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.6","order":"02.03.005.5061"},["b","6"],"And Pharaoh commanded the same day the taskmasters of the people, and their officers, saying,"],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.7","order":"02.03.005.5062"},["b","7"],"Ye shall no more give the people straw to make brick, as heretofore: let them go and gather straw for themselves."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.8","order":"02.03.005.5063"},["b","8"],"And the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_8a"},"tale"],"of the bricks, which they did make heretofore, ye shall lay upon them; ye shall not diminish",["i","ought"],"thereof: for they",["i","be"],"idle; therefore they cry, saying, Let us go",["i","and"],"sacrifice to our God."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.9","order":"02.03.005.5064"},["b","9"],"Let there more work be laid upon the men, that they may labour therein; and let them not regard vain words."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.10","order":"02.03.005.5065"},["b","10"],"¶And the taskmasters of the people went out, and their officers, and they spake to the people, saying, Thus saith Pharaoh, I will not give you straw."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.11","order":"02.03.005.5066"},["b","11"],"Go ye, get you straw where ye can find it: yet",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"not ought of"],"your work shall be diminished."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.12","order":"02.03.005.5067"},["b","12"],"So the people were scattered abroad throughout all the land of Egypt to gather stubble instead of straw."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.13","order":"02.03.005.5068"},["b","13"],"And the taskmasters",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"hasted"],["i","them,"],"saying, Fulfil your works,",["i","your"],"daily tasks, as when there was straw."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.14","order":"02.03.005.5069"},["b","14"],"And the officers of the children of Israel, which Pharaoh’s taskmasters had set over them, were beaten,",["i","and"],"demanded, Wherefore have ye not fulfilled your task in making brick both yesterday and to day, as heretofore?"],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.15","order":"02.03.005.5070"},["b","15"],"¶Then the officers of the children of Israel came and cried unto Pharaoh, saying, Wherefore dealest thou thus with thy servants?"],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.16","order":"02.03.005.5071"},["b","16"],"There is no straw given unto thy servants, and they say to us, Make brick: and, behold, thy servants",["i","are"],"beaten; but the fault",["i","is"],"in thine own people."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.17","order":"02.03.005.5072"},["b","17"],"But he said, Ye",["i","are"],"idle,",["i","ye are"],"idle: therefore ye say, Let us go",["i","and"],"do sacrifice to the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.18","order":"02.03.005.5073"},["b","18"],"Go therefore now,",["i","and"],"work; for there shall no straw be given you, yet shall ye deliver the tale of bricks."],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.19","order":"02.03.005.5074"},["b","19"],"And the officers of the children of Israel did see",["i","that"],"they",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_19a"},["i","were"],"in evil",["i","case"]],["i",","],"after it was said, Ye shall not minish",["i","ought"],"from your bricks of your daily task."],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.20","order":"02.03.005.5075"},["b","20"],"¶And they met Moses and Aaron, who stood in the way, as they came forth from Pharaoh:"],["div",{"id":"21","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.21","order":"02.03.005.5076"},["b","21"],"And they said unto them, The",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"look upon you, and judge; because ye have made",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_21a"},"our"],"savour to be",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_21b"},"abhorred"],"in the eyes of Pharaoh, and in the eyes of his servants, to put a sword in their hand to slay us."],["div",{"id":"22","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.22","order":"02.03.005.5077"},["b","22"],"And Moses",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_22a"},"returned"],"unto the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", and said, Lord, wherefore hast thou",["i","so"],["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_22b"},"evil entreated"],"this people? why",["i","is"],"it",["i","that"],"thou hast sent me?"],["div",{"id":"23","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.23","order":"02.03.005.5078"},["b","23"],"For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in thy name, he hath done evil to this people; neither hast thou delivered thy people at all."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.1a","order":"02.03.005.5079"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/3.18"},"Ex. 3:18"],"."],["div",{"id":"1b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.1b","order":"02.03.005.5081"},["b","1b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/17.25.23-29"},"1 Ne. 17:25 (23–29)"],"."],["div",{"id":"1c","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.1c","order":"02.03.005.5083"},["b","1c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/10.9"},"Ex. 10:9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/12.14"},"12:14"],"."],["div",{"id":"2a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.2a","order":"02.03.005.5085"},["b","2a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/9.17"},"Ex. 9:17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/10.3"},"10:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/9.6"},"Alma 9:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.16"},"Moses 5:16"],"."],["div",{"id":"2b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.2b","order":"02.03.005.5087"},["b","2b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/god-knowledge-about"},"TG God, Knowledge about"],"."],["div",{"id":"3a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.3a","order":"02.03.005.5089"},["b","3a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/3.18"},"Ex. 3:18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/7.16"},"7:16"],"."],["div",{"id":"4a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.4a","order":"02.03.005.5091"},["b","4a"],["span.small","HEB"],"hinder, deter."],["div",{"id":"4b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.4b","order":"02.03.005.5093"},["b","4b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/2.11"},"Ex. 2:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/6.6.6-7"},"6:6 (6–7)"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.5a","order":"02.03.005.5095"},["b","5a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/1.12"},"Ex. 1:12"],"."],["div",{"id":"8a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.8a","order":"02.03.005.5097"},["b","8a"],["span.small","OR"],"quota."],["div",{"id":"11a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.11a","order":"02.03.005.5099"},["b","11a"],["span.small","OR"],"none of."],["div",{"id":"13a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.13a","order":"02.03.005.5101"},["b","13a"],["span.small","OR"],"urged."],["div",{"id":"19a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.19a","order":"02.03.005.5103"},["b","19a"],"Hebrew idiom meaning “found themselves in trouble.”"],["div",{"id":"21a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.21a","order":"02.03.005.5105"},["b","21a"],["span.small","HEB"],"us as an offensive savor."],["div",{"id":"21b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.21b","order":"02.03.005.5107"},["b","21b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/14.12.11-12"},"Ex. 14:12 (11–12)"],"."],["div",{"id":"22a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.22a","order":"02.03.005.5109"},["b","22a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/121.2.1-6"},"D&C 121:2 (1–6)"],"."],["div",{"id":"22b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ex/5.22b","order":"02.03.005.5111"},["b","22b"],["span.small","OR"],"badly treated."]]}
